Just 47 percent of farmworkers reported having health insurance, according to the latest National Agricultural Workers Survey.
One of the side effects is that farmworkers are facing an increased level of food insecurity.
Food pantries are also running out of food, according to farmworkers and advocates who spoke to Grist.
The United Farm Workers union polled farmworkers via social media networks to determine whether employers are providing any coronavirus-related information.
Many of the areas that employ farmworkers tend to be rural and lack the health care and other infrastructure to respond to a potential outbreak.